---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Leo Sutton — Finance & Commercial Senior Manager"
  description="Professional profile for Leo Sutton, Finance & Commercial Senior Manager at Unity Advisory, focused on finance transformation, ERP implementation, change management, AI consulting, and PMO."
>
  <section class="hero container" aria-labelledby="page-title">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="eyebrow">Professional profile</p>
      <h1 id="page-title">Leo Sutton</h1>
      <p class="hero-summary">
        Finance & Commercial Senior Manager at Unity Advisory, with experience in finance transformation, ERP implementation, change management, AI consulting, and PMO.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Primary actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/leopoldsutton/">Contact on LinkedIn</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <figure class="hero-photo-card" aria-label="Portrait of Leo Sutton">
      <img src="/leo-sutton-profile.jpg" alt="Portrait of Leo Sutton in a navy jacket and white shirt" width="2560" height="1707" loading="eager" decoding="async" />
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section id="profile" class="section">
    <div class="container section-grid">
      <div><h2>Profile</h2></div>
      <div>
        <p class="lede">
          I work with organisations on finance and commercial transformation: improving processes, systems, governance, and delivery across complex change programmes.
        </p>
        <p>
          My background combines consulting delivery, enterprise technology, and practical operating discipline. I am particularly interested in how finance teams can use better systems, clearer governance, and well-scoped AI tools to make work more reliable.
        </p>
        <div class="meta-grid" aria-label="Profile summary">
          <div>
            <span class="meta-label">Current role</span>
            <strong>Finance & Commercial Senior Manager, Unity Advisory</strong>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="meta-label">Previous experience</span>
            <strong>Deloitte UK — Enterprise Technology & Performance</strong>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="meta-label">Location</span>
            <strong>London, UK</strong>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="meta-label">Professional focus</span>
            <strong>Finance transformation, ERP, change, AI, PMO</strong>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="focus" class="section">
    <div class="container section-grid">
      <div><h2>Focus areas</h2></div>
      <div>
        <p class="lede">Work centred on finance and commercial transformation, from design through delivery.</p>
        <div class="cards">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Finance transformation</h3>
            <p>Process, operating model, reporting, controls, and ways of working across finance functions.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>ERP implementation</h3>
            <p>Supporting technology-enabled change where finance processes, data, controls, and adoption need to align.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Change management</h3>
            <p>Helping teams move from design to adoption through communication, governance, stakeholder management, and delivery discipline.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>AI consulting</h3>
            <p>Practical use of AI in professional workflows, with attention to security, governance, and where automation is genuinely useful.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>PMO</h3>
            <p>Programme structure, planning cadence, issue management, decision tracking, and senior stakeholder reporting.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Governance</h3>
            <p>Experience outside consulting includes trustee, school governor, CIC director, and lodge leadership responsibilities.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="experience" class="section">
    <div class="container section-grid">
      <div><h2>Experience</h2></div>
      <div>
        <ol class="timeline" aria-label="Professional experience">
          <li>
            <div class="timeline-heading">
              <h3>Unity Advisory</h3>
              <span>Finance & Commercial Senior Manager</span>
            </div>
            <p>Advisory work across finance, commercial, transformation, and technology-enabled change.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="timeline-heading">
              <h3>Deloitte UK</h3>
              <span>Enterprise Technology & Performance</span>
            </div>
            <p>Nearly a decade in consulting, with work across finance transformation, ERP implementation, change management, AI consulting, and PMO.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="work" class="section">
    <div class="container section-grid">
      <div><h2>How I work</h2></div>
      <div>
        <p class="lede">I value clear scope, practical governance, and decisions that are easy to explain.</p>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>Start with the business problem, not the tool or framework.</li>
          <li>Make priorities, trade-offs, owners, and decision points explicit.</li>
          <li>Keep governance useful: enough structure to help delivery, not more.</li>
          <li>Use AI and automation selectively, with appropriate controls and human judgement.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="contact" class="section">
    <div class="container contact-panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
      <h2>Professional enquiries</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        For conversations about finance transformation, ERP implementation, change management, AI consulting, or PMO, please contact me on
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/leopoldsutton/">LinkedIn</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
